      "highlights": [
        "General Search allows the user to search by docket number, accession number, and many other criteria. It is the only search which allows the user to perform a keyword search.The result of a General search will include all documents that possess an accession number. This may include documents that do not possess a docket number.It will not include migrated FAMIS data. (See Docket Search for FAMIS data.) Docket Search requires the user to enter a valid docket number and a date range to obtain a result.It will display dockets based on the following rules: (1) docket number was generated within the create or filing date range provided by the user, and (2) the docket number possess an accession number.It will not display dockets whose filing or create date was outside the range provided. FAMIS data may be included by checking the FAMIS checkbox.New Docket Search will search repositories outside of eLibrary (ATMS) for new dockets. Users may search by Create Date or Filed Date as well as date range between 1-10 days.The create date boundaries are from 06/06/2004 to the current date. Enter a partial or complete docket number. For multiple entries, separate each docket number with a comma.If you enter a sub-docket number, the sub-docket field will be disabled and ignored in the search. See the Search Tips link on this page to learn more about docket and sub-docket search.Filed Date is the date a document is received and stamped by the Office of the Secretary. The Document Date is the date on the face of the document.The Posted Date is the date that a document is published in eLibrary. The Create Date (New Docket Search Only) is the date the docket / sub-docket was created in FERC Online Administration (FOLA)."
